The President of the United States, Donald Trump, has accused the Democratic presidential candidate, Joe Biden, of taking performance-enhancing drugs for his public speeches. President Trump made the claim during an interview with Fox News, Daily Times reports. It is due to be broadcast in full on Saturday. He said, “I think there are probably, possibly drugs involved, that’s what I hear.” READ ALSO: Biden breaks Obama’s record as campaign raises $364 million online Trump, for a long time, has looked to paint 77-year-old Biden as senile and incompetent as part of his campaign tactics to discredit the qualification of his opposite number for the job. The US President also stated that he was not disturbed regarding the possibility of violence on the day of the election. Speaking boldly to the press, Trump said, “We’ll put them down very quickly if they do that.”